<div class="index-item-long-text"><div class="truncatable"><div class="truncatable-content"><div class="index-item-long-text-content"><hr />
<h2>MVP Definition: "Grant Copilot"</h2>
<h3>Core Concept</h3>
<p>A conversational AI that answers PI questions about their grants in plain English. No forms, no navigation, no training required.</p>
<h3>Minimum Data Model</h3>
<pre><code>GRANT:
  - name/id (e.g., &quot;NIH R01 GM123456&quot;)
  - total_amount
  - start_date, end_date  
  - remaining_balance
  - restrictions (free text - AI interprets)

INSTITUTIONAL CONTEXT:
  - F&amp;A rate (e.g., 55%)
  - Fringe rate (e.g., 32%)
</code></pre>
<p>That's it. A PI enters this in 5 minutes per grant via conversation, not forms.</p>
<hr />
<h3>MVP Feature Set</h3>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Category</th>
<th>Queries Supported</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><strong>Balance</strong></td>
<td>"How much is left on my R01?" / "Which grant has most flexibility?"</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Feasibility</strong></td>
<td>"Can I hire a summer student?" / "Can I buy $15K equipment?"</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Projections</strong></td>
<td>"Will I run out before grant ends?" / "What if I hire a postdoc in March?"</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Restrictions</strong></td>
<td>"Can I use this for international travel?" / "Which grants allow participant payments?"</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<h3>Explicitly NOT in MVP</h3>
<ul>
<li>Pre-award / proposal building</li>
<li>Expense tracking (just balances)</li>
<li>Multi-user / lab sharing</li>
<li>System integrations</li>
<li>Compliance reporting</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h3>User Flow: First 5 Minutes</h3>
<pre><code>[Landing]
&quot;Ask questions about your research funding in plain English&quot;
→ Get Started

[Conversational Setup]
AI: &quot;What's your F&amp;A rate?&quot;
You: &quot;55%&quot;
AI: &quot;Fringe rate?&quot;  
You: &quot;32%&quot;
AI: &quot;Tell me about your first grant.&quot;
You: &quot;R01 from NIH, GM123456, $1.2M over 5 years, started Sept 2023, 
      about $400K left, no equipment over $5K&quot;
AI: &quot;Added. Want to add another or ask something?&quot;

[First Query]
You: &quot;Can I hire a summer undergrad?&quot;
AI: &quot;Yes. 
     - Stipend: $6,000
     - Fringe (32%): $1,920
     - F&amp;A (55%): $4,356
     - Total: $12,276

     You'd have ~$387,724 remaining through Aug 2028.
     NIH R01s allow undergrad training, no prior approval needed.&quot;
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Value delivered in under 5 minutes.</strong></p>
<hr />
<h3>Technical Architecture</h3>
<pre><code>┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐
│           Chat Interface (PWA)          │
│         Mobile-first, offline-capable   │
└─────────────────┬───────────────────────┘
                  │
┌─────────────────▼───────────────────────┐
│              API Layer                  │
│           (FastAPI / Node)              │
└─────────────────┬───────────────────────┘
                  │
     ┌────────────┴────────────┐
     ▼                         ▼
┌─────────────┐       ┌─────────────────┐
│   SQLite    │       │   Claude API    │
│  (grants,   │       │  (NL parsing,   │
│  settings)  │       │   reasoning,    │
│             │       │   calculations) │
└─────────────┘       └─────────────────┘
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Key constraints:</strong>
- &lt; 500KB initial load (works on 3G)
- SQLite = zero infrastructure, single-file database
- Data exportable, user-owned, no lock-in
- Can run hosted OR self-hosted OR local</p>
<hr />
<h3>What Makes This Different from a Spreadsheet</h3>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Spreadsheet</th>
<th>Grant Copilot</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Write formulas</td>
<td>Ask questions</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Maintain structure</td>
<td>No maintenance</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Look up rules manually</td>
<td>Built-in sponsor knowledge</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Static</td>
<td>Scenario modeling ("what if I hire...")</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Generic</td>
<td>Research-domain specific</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<hr />
<h3>Success Criteria</h3>
<ol>
<li><strong>Time to value</strong>: &lt; 5 minutes to first useful answer</li>
<li><strong>Calculation accuracy</strong>: &gt; 95%</li>
<li><strong>Global accessibility</strong>: Works on 3G, &lt; 500KB</li>
<li><strong>Retention</strong>: 50%+ return within 7 days</li>
</ol>
<hr />
<h3>Build Estimate</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Solo developer</strong>: 4-6 weeks</li>
<li><strong>Small team (2-3)</strong>: 2-3 weeks</li>
<li><strong>Core complexity</strong>: Prompt engineering + domain knowledge encoding, not infrastructure</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h3>Open Questions for Discussion</h3>
<ol>
<li>
<p><strong>Hosted vs. local-first</strong>: Start with hosted SaaS for simplicity, or prioritize self-hosted/local for data sovereignty?</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>LLM choice</strong>: Claude API (best reasoning) vs. open models (lower cost, offline capable)?</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Onboarding depth</strong>: Conversational only, or also support CSV/paste import for faster bulk setup?</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Institutional knowledge</strong>: How deep to encode sponsor rules (NIH, NSF, Wellcome, etc.) vs. letting users specify restrictions?</p>
</li>
</ol>
<p>Which of these do you want to dig into?</p></div></div><button class="expand-btn">Show more</button></div></div>
