<td>Conference presence, word-of-mouth, champion users, maybe a paper</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Sustainability model unclear</strong></td>
<td>HIGH</td>
<td>Open core with premium tier, or foundation funding, or both</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<hr />
<h3>The "Spendlab Problem"</h3>
<p>Spendlab's existence is the biggest strategic challenge. Key facts from <a href="https://www.spendlab.org/">their site</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>"It started in a single lab and is now used by researchers across the world... at more than 60 universities"</p>
<p>"Your budget data never travels over the internet... We run all calculations on your own computer"</p>
<p>"$150/year for labs under $250K... $400/year unlimited"</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Spendlab chose local-first privacy over cloud AI.</strong> This is a meaningful tradeoff:</p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Their Choice</th>
<th>Your Opportunity</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Local-only = no AI possible</td>
<td>Cloud = AI-native experience</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Post-award only</td>
<td>Pre + post-award lifecycle</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Visualization-first</td>
<td>Conversation-first</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Manual planning</td>
<td>"Can I hire a summer student?"</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>No sponsor knowledge</td>
<td>Built-in NIH/NSF/Wellcome rules</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<hr />
<h3>Differentiation Matrix</h3>
<pre><code>                    AI-Native    Pre-Award    Global Access    PI-First
                    ─────────    ─────────    ─────────────    ────────
Spendlab               ✗            ✗              ~             ✓
Cayuse/Kuali           ✗            ✓              ✗             ✗
Workday/Banner         ✗            ~              ✗             ✗
Univ. Dashboards       ✗            ✗              ✗             ~
THIS PROJECT           ✓            ✓              ✓             ✓
</code></pre>
<hr />
<h3>Critical Success Factors</h3>
<p>For this to succeed despite the competition:</p>
<ol>
<li>
<p><strong>AI accuracy must be exceptional</strong> - One wrong answer about grant spending destroys trust forever. Invest heavily in prompt engineering for sponsor rules.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Pre-award must be dramatically better than Excel</strong> - If it's just "okay," nobody switches. Auto-calculate F&amp;A, fringe, yearly increases. Export to sponsor formats.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Solve data freshness without integration</strong> - Make reconciliation painless: "Your R01 shows $400K - still accurate?" Accept statement uploads.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Global-first, not global-later</strong> - Multi-currency, languages, free tier from day 1. Partner with <a href="https://scienceforafrica.foundation/africa-research-management-capacity-strengthening-programme">REMACS</a>, Science for Africa.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Open source credibility</strong> - Academic communities trust open. Build in public, accept contributions, maybe publish a paper.</p>
</li>
</ol>
<hr />
<h3>Honest Assessment</h3>
<p><strong>The opportunity is real.</strong> The 42% administrative burden on federally-funded researchers (<a href="https://exlibrisgroup.com/blog/research-administration-relieving-the-pressure-on-researchers/">per NSF</a>) and Spendlab's traction prove demand exists.</p>
<p><strong>But Spendlab is already there.</strong> This can't just be "another budget tool." The differentiators must be:
- AI-native (nobody has this yet)
- Pre-award lifecycle (Spendlab lacks this)
- Global accessibility (enterprises ignore this)</p>
<p>Without those being <strong>excellent</strong>, this is a me-too product in a market where Spendlab already has word-of-mouth in academic circles.</p>
<hr />
<h3>Questions This Raises</h3>
<ol>
<li>
<p><strong>Compete or complement Spendlab?</strong> Could this be positioned as "Spendlab + AI layer" rather than a replacement?</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Pre-award scope?</strong> How deep into proposal development? Just budgets, or also narrative assistance, compliance checking?</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Privacy tradeoff messaging?</strong> Spendlab's local-only approach is a selling point for some. How do you message "yes your data goes to the cloud, but you get AI"?</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Foundation funding vs. commercial?</strong> Global accessibility may require grant funding. Does that conflict with building a sustainable product?</p>
</li>
</ol>
<p>Want to dig into any of these strategic questions?</p></div></div><button class="expand-btn">Show more</button></div></div>
