<h2>Revised Framing</h2>
<p>You're right. I was thinking too small on pre-award and wrong on AI.</p>
<h3>Pre-Award: Portfolio Memory</h3>
<p>It's not about building budgets. It's about <strong>tracking your entire funding effort</strong>:</p>
<pre><code>┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    PROPOSAL PORTFOLIO                        │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  R01 GM-xxxxx    │ Submitted 2024-02 │ Funded   │ $1.2M    │
│  R01 AI-xxxxx    │ Submitted 2024-06 │ Declined │ Score 32 │
│  R21 GM-xxxxx    │ Submitted 2024-09 │ Pending  │ ---      │
│  NSF CAREER      │ Draft             │ ---      │ ---      │
│  Wellcome Trust  │ Submitted 2023-11 │ Declined │ Revising │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Value of tracking unfunded proposals:</strong>
- Annual reporting ("I submitted 5 proposals this year")
- Tenure packages (shows effort, not just success)
- Resubmission tracking (A1 from A0, what changed)
- Repurposing (aims from declined R01 → new R21)
- Pattern recognition (which study sections, which POs)</p>
<p><strong>Spendlab has none of this.</strong> It only knows grants after they're funded.</p>
<hr />
<h3>AI: Evaluation, Not Generation</h3>
<p>You're not asking AI to write grants. You're asking AI to <strong>help you understand and honor your commitments</strong>:</p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Query</th>
<th>What AI Does</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>"What did I promise in Year 2?"</td>
<td>Searches your funded proposal, extracts timeline/milestones</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>"Can I hire a computational person?"</td>
<td>Checks if you budgeted for this role, or proposed wet-lab only</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>"Is this equipment purchase in scope?"</td>
<td>Compares request against your proposed methods/budget</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>"Which grant could support phage work?"</td>
<td>Searches across all proposals for relevant aims</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>"Do I need to notify NIH about this pivot?"</td>
<td>Compares new direction against original scope, flags if &gt;25% change</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p><strong>The AI is a query layer over your own documents</strong> - not a generative tool.</p>
<p>PIs forget what they wrote. Proposals are 12-page documents submitted months or years ago. The AI becomes <strong>institutional memory for your own commitments</strong>.</p>
<hr />
<h3>Why This Changes the Competitive Picture</h3>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
