<h2>De Novo Design: PI-Native, Not Finance-Native</h2>
<h3>The Core Insight</h3>
<p>Your shadow spreadsheet is complex because it mirrors Workday's complexity. The system we build should mirror <strong>how PIs actually think</strong>, not how finance systems work.</p>
<hr />
<h3>How PIs Actually Think</h3>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>PI Mental Model</th>
<th>Finance System Model</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>"My R01"</td>
<td>GR0035527 / AW00013543 / Fund 12345</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>"About $80K left"</td>
<td>$79,847.23 actuals + $2,341.00 encumbrances - $1,547.89 pending</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>"The Diamond collaboration"</td>
<td>Cost center 4472, worktag SP-00234, grant 6929</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>"Can I hire someone?"</td>
<td>Navigate 5 screens, interpret 3 account codes</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>"Supplies"</td>
<td>Account codes 6240-6249</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p><strong>Build for the left column, not the right.</strong></p>
<hr />
<h3>What PIs Actually Need to Know</h3>
<p><strong>About Money:</strong>
- How much can I spend?
- Can I afford X?
- Am I going to run out?</p>
<p><strong>About People:</strong>
- Who works for me?
- Who's paid by what?
- Can I hire someone?</p>
<p><strong>About Time:</strong>
- When does this end?
- What deadlines are coming?</p>
<p><strong>About Commitments:</strong>
- What did I promise?
- Am I on track?</p>
<p><strong>About History:</strong>
- What have I applied for?
- What's my track record?</p>
<hr />
<h3>The Simplest Viable Data Model</h3>
<pre><code>GRANTS (funding sources)
├── name: &quot;My R01&quot; (what YOU call it)
├── sponsor: NIH
├── available_funds: $87,000 (one number you update)
├── end_date: 2026-06-30
├── purpose: &quot;Microbiome research&quot; (your words)
├── restrictions: &quot;No equipment over $5K&quot; (your words)
└── proposal_doc: [uploaded PDF for AI to query]

PEOPLE (your team)
├── name: &quot;Doug Kwon&quot;
├── role: &quot;Postdoc&quot;
└── funded_by: [&quot;My R01&quot;]

PROPOSALS (what you've applied for)
├── title: &quot;Mechanisms of gut immunity&quot;
├── sponsor: NIH
├── submitted: 2024-06-15
├── status: pending | funded | declined
├── document: [uploaded for AI to remember]
└── outcome: score, critiques, notes
</code></pre>
<p><strong>That's it.</strong> No chart of accounts. No worktags. No fund hierarchies.</p>
<hr />
<h3>Data Input Philosophy</h3>
<p><strong>We don't recreate the ledger. We capture what PIs know.</strong></p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Data</th>
<th>How It Gets In</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><strong>Proposals</strong></td>
<td>Upload PDF, AI extracts structure, you confirm</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Awards</strong></td>
<td>"This got funded" → link to proposal, enter amount/dates</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Balances</strong></td>
<td>"I have about $80K left" (you update when you check)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>People</strong></td>
<td>Add once, update when things change</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p><strong>Key principle: Approximate is fine.</strong></p>
<p>A PI doesn't make $50 decisions. They make $5,000+ decisions. "About $80K left" is just as useful as "$79,847.23 after encumbrances" for answering "Can I hire a summer student?"</p>
<hr />
<h3>The Trade-Off We Make</h3>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>What We Give Up</th>
<th>What We Gain</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Transaction-level accuracy</td>
<td>Answers to actual questions</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Audit-ready financials</td>
<td>Speed and simplicity</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Integration with Workday</td>
<td>Independence from Workday</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Institutional compliance</td>
<td>Individual PI utility</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Precision</td>
<td>Usability</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p><strong>This is not a finance system. It's a PI decision-support system.</strong></p>
<p>For compliance and audits, Workday still exists. This system answers "Can I?" not "Did I?"</p>
<hr />
<h3>Example Interaction</h3>
<pre><code>You: &quot;Add a grant&quot;

AI: &quot;What do you call this grant?&quot;
You: &quot;Fresh R01&quot;

AI: &quot;Who funds it?&quot;
You: &quot;NIH&quot;

AI: &quot;How much is available to spend right now?&quot;
You: &quot;About $87,000&quot;

AI: &quot;When does it end?&quot;
You: &quot;June 2026&quot;

AI: &quot;What's it for? (optional - helps me answer questions later)&quot;
You: &quot;Microbiome and gut immunity&quot;

AI: &quot;Any restrictions I should know about?&quot;
You: &quot;No equipment over $5K&quot;

AI: &quot;Got it. Fresh R01 added.
