<h3>The Build Question</h3>
<p><strong>Option A: Core First, Procurement Later</strong></p>
<pre><code>Phase 1: Proposals, Awards, Personnel, Budgets, AI
Phase 2: Add Procurement module
Phase 3: Integrations (LIMS, ELN, etc.)
</code></pre>
<p><em>Pros: Focused, achievable MVP</em>
<em>Cons: Early users still do manual spending entry</em></p>
<p><strong>Option B: Include Procurement from Start</strong></p>
<pre><code>Phase 1: Everything including item-level tracking
</code></pre>
<p><em>Pros: Complete data flow, no manual entry</em>
<em>Cons: Much larger scope, longer to MVP</em></p>
<p><strong>Option C: Core + Procurement Integration</strong></p>
<pre><code>Phase 1: Core + integrate Lab Spend for procurement
</code></pre>
<p><em>Pros: Item-level tracking via existing tool</em>
<em>Cons: Dependency, Lab Spend is US-focused</em></p>
<hr />
<h3>For Global Accessibility</h3>
<p>The <strong>modular approach</strong> matters here:</p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Context</th>
<th>What They Use</th>
</tr>
</thead>
